cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Put some #baking trays{} in your oven.

> You may be able to fit two pizzas on one tray, depending on the size of your tray, or use two trays if necessary.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Put a #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} and add your garlic. Cook for
~{1%minute} before pouring in the @tomato passata{1}. Sprinkle in a pinch of @salt{} and a
grind of @black pepper{} and stir everything together. Simmer gently for ~{5-6%minutes},
then remove the pan from the heat. This is your tomato sauce.

While your tomato sauce is simmering you can get on with the rest of the prep. Cut each
@chestnut mushrooms{1}(cut into roughly four slices) into roughly four slices. Cut the
@red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice into thin half moon shapes.

Now it's time to roll out the pizza dough! Dust your work surface with some
@flour{} (if you have some). Alternatively, place your @pizza dough{2} between two large
sheets of #clingfilm{} (so it doesn't stick to your work surface!). Roll out into round
pizza bases roughly 25cm across.

> If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle wrapped in clingfilm.

Carefully take your baking trays out of your oven and place your pizza bases on them.
Divide your tomato sauce between each pizza base, then with the back of a #spoon{}, spread
it over each pizza base using swirling motions. Leave a 1cm gap around the edge.

Dot teaspoonfuls of the @mascarpone cheese{1} on top, then lay on your mushrooms.
Sprinkle over the @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}.

Season with some @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Pop your pizzas in your oven
for ~{15-20%minutes}, until the dough is golden and the cheese is bubbling.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't brown too much!

Put your onion in a saucepan on medium heat with a glug of @oil{} and cook for
~{7%minutes} until soft. Pour in the @balsamic vinegar{1} and stir together. Turn the
heat down to low and cook for another ~{7-10%minutes} until your onion is soft and
caramelised.

Once your pizzas are ready, remove them from your oven and spoon your caramelised
onion on top. Put a handful of @wild rocket{1%handful} on each pizza and devour!